	abstract = {In this context, the impact of exploitation on demersal resources and on fish diversity in the Gulf of Lions becomes a relevant question. [...] - Distribution of expérimental trawl hauls in the Gulf of Lions from 1957 to 1995. [...] Firstly an exhaustive list of fish species caught on the continental shelf and on the slope was established. [...] Data from twenty species or gênera could be used, the list of which is given in table II. [...] Landings for thèse species représentée! 53 to 70 \% of the total demersal fish landings in individual years (mean over years 65\%). [...] - Rank-frequency diagrams for elasmobranch species on the continental shelf and on the slope of the Gulf of Lions. Correspondence between abbreviated and full names is given in appendix 1. [...] The décline of elasmobranchs began on the continental shelf as far back as the sixties and was quite obvious in the year 1980-84. [...] gênerai shape of the diagrams and in ranks of the species : the disappearance of a given species may often be foreseen from a décline in rank. [...] DISCUSSION Due to the qualitative value of surveys data base, only descriptive methods were available to point out and to describe possible changes in groundfish diversity. [...] The total number of species fished in the Gulf of Lions was quite stable throughout the time period.},
